<TABLE CLASS="SPELLS" WIDTH=100%>
<TR><TH>Evensong<BR>
<I><FONT SIZE=-1>Posted 2000-01-21 19:41:53 by Cipramil</FONT></I></TH></TR>
<TR><TD>What people fail to realise is that the actual damage info sent by the server to the client (which is what this database shows, in case you hadn't realised) is BASE DAMAGE. You add the caster's LEVEL * 2 to this value to get the actual damage. Therefore, at level 12, Bellow does 1 + ( 12 / 2 )= 7 points of damage. Simple.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
